section.t:
Mapping of Address and Port with Encapsulation (MAP-E) is described in . MAP-E requires the provisioning of the following per-subscriber information at the customer edge device:
whether the device is to operate in mesh or hub-and-spoke mode;
the IPv6 address of the border router, also known as the Default Mapping rule;
the specially constructed End-user IPv6 prefix for the customer edge device. suggests that this would be supplied as part of normal IPv6 provisioning, so it can be ignored as a requirement here.
the Basic Mapping Rule for the customer edge device. This includes the following parameters:
the rule IPv6 prefix and length;
the rule IPv4 prefix and length;
the number of "Extended Address" (EA) bits included in the End-user IPv6 prefix;
of those Extended Address bits, the number that precede the port set identifier. This is currently a matter of discussion, whether it should default to 4 or 6 or be fixed at either of these values.
in mesh mode only, zero or more Forwarding Mapping Rules, containing the same parameters as the Basic Mapping rule.
optionally, the port set identifier if the EA bits do carry it.

It appears that the following items are common to two or more
        methods and should therefore be specified in method-independent
        fashion:
        
          the IPv6 address of the border router;
          
          an IPv4 prefix and length (could be a /32);
          
          a port set identifier;
          
          tentatively, a method indicator, indicating which of the
          above transition methods the customer edge device must use.

The remaining requirements are method-specific:
        
          for DS-Lite, the identity of the NAT pool to which the subscriber
          is assigned;
          
          for Public 4over6 and LW4o6, a binding between a customer IPv6
          prefix or address and an IPv4 address;
          
          for MAP-E, the indication of whether mesh mode or hub-and-spoke
          mode is to be used;
          
          for MAP-E, a Grouped AVP expressing a MAP Rule.

figure.artwork:
4to6-Binding  ::= < AVP Header: TBD07 >
                 { IPv4-Prefix-Or-Addr }
                 { IPv6-Prefix-Or-Addr }
              0*1{ Port-Set-Identifier }
                *[ AVP ]

MAP-Rule      ::= < AVP Header: TBD08 >
                 { IPv4-Prefix-Or-Addr }
                 { IPv6-Prefix-Or-Addr }
                 { EA-Field-Length     }
                 [ PSID-Offset         ]
                *[ AVP ]
